{
  "texts": [
    "Bins are traversed from chromosome start to end separately for each of the five basic SV types.",
    "Neighboring bins are merged if the inner distance between them is smaller than a threshold calculated based on the minimum standard deviation of the genomic SV start positions within each bin.",
    "The inner distance threshold d n is calculated as d n = r ⋅ min(σ StartA, σ StartB), where r is a constant (default, 2.5), and σ StartA and σ StartB refer to the standard deviation of indicated SV start positions in the two neighboring bins, respectively.",
    "In regions spanning tandem repeats, a more relaxed clustering criterion is applied.",
    "Neighboring bins are also clustered when their outer distance falls below a threshold defined based on the indicated average SV length of the SV signals stored in the neighboring bins."
  ]
}